  <div class="well">
    <p>The goal is to "sink" all of your opponent's ships before they sink yours.</p>
    <p>Your opponent <!-- can be -->is another person<!--  or the computer -->. </p>
    <p><!-- When playing with two people, t -->The first person ready with their ships moves first. <!-- You always move first against the computer. --></p>
    <p>You see two grids. The one on the right represents your opponent's sea. This is where you click a grid space to "fire" and hopefully hit one of their ships. In this version, you only get one shot per turn. The grid on the left is your sea.</p>
    <p>Before play begins, you secretly arrange your ships on the left grid.</p>
    <p>Each ship occupies a number of consecutive squares on the grid, arranged either horizontally or vertically. Only one ship can occupy any square in the grid. Each player has the same type of ship fleet. The number of squares for each ship is determined by the type of the ship.</p>
    <p>
      <div class="row">
        <span class="col-sm-1 col-sm-offset-1 h5">Quantity</span>
